Beautiful Humpback Whales Encounters by @rachelsawden in Bermuda 🇧🇲 🐋💙
•
•
“March-April is whale season in Bermuda where nearly 10,000 humpback whales pass our shores. These whales are on a migration north to the rich feeding waters near Labrador, Greenland, and Iceland. I was lucky enough to get out a few times last month and extra lucky to observe some very active whales. Before this year, I had only really seen them blow and pop their flukes out to dive, but this time I saw lots of breaches, tail slapping, fin slapping, and a spy hop. In between the breaches of one very energetic whale, a pod of dolphins came to check us out and do some bow riding. Swipe to see all of the action!
🌺🌺🌺🌺
📷 Video courtesy: @rachelsawden & @james.doughty
